parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause overheating, steam to build up in the vehicle interior, and hot coolant to leak into the passenger's foot area, impairing visibility and potentially causing burns.
symptoms: steam building up in the vehicle interior
hot coolant leaking into the passenger's foot area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing belt failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power and control, which can lead to accidents.

Engine mount failure can cause vibration, noise, and engine damage, which can lead to accidents.
Engine valve failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power and control, which can lead to accidents.
Intermittent stalling can cause loss of power and control, which can lead to accidents.
The failure of the heater core can cause the release of antifreeze fumes and steam into the passenger compartment, impairing the driver's visibility, and potentially causing respiratory issues.

antifreeze fumes and smells are emitted from the vents

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater control switch can cause damage to the dash panel and potentially lead to a fire hazard.

causing damage to the dash panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Windshield pitting can impair the driver's visibility and potentially cause accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning fuel tank sending unit can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to engine stalling or failure, and potentially causing accidents.

symptoms: Vehicle stopped due to lack of fuel
